64d019520c6622478a97fa50be9d8bc4 (16:52): do u recognize this error ? "no loaded modules provide ppp(ppp_start)" ??
c6c892610f6fe6b722f8de240a53cb45 (16:53): you dont have the ppp driver installed - you either havent set up /etc/conf.d/net properly (ie its looking for ppp when you dont want it.)
c6c892610f6fe6b722f8de240a53cb45 (16:55): do you have rp-pppoe installed?
c6c892610f6fe6b722f8de240a53cb45 (16:56): i havent actually set it up before - docs or gentoo-wiki should help

c6c892610f6fe6b722f8de240a53cb45 (16:57): and it hasnt actually worked yet?
64d019520c6622478a97fa50be9d8bc4 (16:57): i think it could be because i didn't wrote the correct password
c6c892610f6fe6b722f8de240a53cb45 (16:58): that error means it cant find the ppp driver, which is strange since you have rp-pppoe install
64d019520c6622478a97fa50be9d8bc4 (16:58): it's not my first pppoe install
c6c892610f6fe6b722f8de240a53cb45 (16:58): sorry i cant help much more than that
